<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="1668" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1668">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.114M69/125.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Pera</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-15">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 15, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Fowle and Upham returned today.<note n="2" xml:id="d1668fn2">See
                                telegrams of May 3.</note> I will cable you tomorrow the conclusions
                            of their investigation.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Rockhill</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>